    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nLSP diagnostic signs disappear one second after entering insert mode, only to reappear after leaving insert mode.\r\n\r\nThis leads thel code \"jumping\" when insert mode  is entered due to the sign column disappearing. \r\n\r\nThis is the closest thing I could find in the help (the default seems to be what I want, but the behavior is unwanted since diagnostics *are* updated):\r\n\r\n    :helpgrep update_in_insert\r\n    update_in_insert: (default false) Update diagnostics in\r\n    Insert mode (if false, diagnostics are updated on\r\n    InsertLeave)\r\n\r\nSimilar issues:\r\n\r\n1. [https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/10z4q16/lsp\\_diagnostics\\_disappear\\_completely\\_in\\_insert/](https://www.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/10z4q16/lsp_diagnostics_disappear_completely_in_insert/)\r\n2. [https://vi.stackexchange.com/questions/42126/neovim-how-to-keep-the-diagnostic-message-in-insert-mode](https://vi.stackexchange.com/questions/42126/neovim-how-to-keep-the-diagnostic-message-in-insert-mode)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- No diagnostics should disappear when entering insert mode.\r\n  - (All diagnostics that were shown before entering insert mode should stay visible until insert mode is leaved)\r\n- No new diagnostics should appear while in insert mode.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There is afaik nothing in Neovim that would change the diagnostics on insert enter by default.\r\n\r\nI also can't reproduce it:\r\n\r\n![recording](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/38700/e8cb673e-db3a-4900-9b17-658e3da12446)\r\n\r\n\r\nMy best guess is that if you enter insert mode and type something, the client notifies the server about the document changes and then the server re-publishes the diagnostics.\r\n\r\nWould need some minimal reproduction steps",
